docs: clarify and rewrite bugs_and_issues.md with technical detail

Rewrote Docs/bugs_and_issues.md to turn vague descriptions into
actionable bug reports. Each entry now includes the exact file and
line number(s) involved, a clear description of current vs. expected
behavior, and a concrete fix strategy.

Changes per bug:

- Bug 1 & 5 (copy save key): clarified that copyGatewayKey() cannot
  be reused as-is since it reads from a DOM element only present in
  the gateway screen; the fix must copy from the saveKey variable.

- Bug 2 (campaign key in creation form): pinpointed both the HTML
  form (aria-player.html) and the JS handler (confirmCreateCharacter)
  that need updating; noted the field is optional.

- Bug 3 & 4 (vials): separated into two distinct problems — vials
  appearing in the Inventory tab when alchemy is disabled (Bug 3),
  and vials missing from the left inventory sidebar regardless of
  state (Bug 4). Documented different visibility rules for each.

- Bug 6 (join code position): identified it as a two-element swap
  in the GM topbar HTML.

- Bug 7 (player count): explained why the count always shows X/X
  (in-memory Map resets on page refresh), and proposed persisting
  known players to localStorage per campaign so the GM can see
  0/6 even after a reload.
